gomodel:SYNGO_5322  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: \"In parallel, we analyzed the effects of Sema4C exposure on dendritic protrusions and observed that Sema4C treatment led to a significant rise in the density of spines in hippocampal neurons (Fig. 6e, f). Pre-incubation with the ROCK inhibitor Y-27632 abolished the Sema4C-mediated increase in spine density (Fig. 6e, f).\". Experimental description: Results, Figure 6 legend: \"Function of Sema4C in fear and fear memory on dendritic structural remodeling ex vivo. a ELISA-based analysis of RhoA activation in cultured mouse hippocampal neurons upon exposure to Sema4C (150 nM for 15 min);\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2023-03-11" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_5322" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

